items.name: Chimera's 9-Way Photoreal Mix
items.description:
I'm no naming genius.

Photoreal is just marketing bs, but yeah, the texture is pretty good. I know it's an oversaturated model type, but hopefully this one has some qualities you'll enjoy.

The product of haphazard experimental alchemy with Supermerger, the outcome was a lot better than I expected. The goals going in pretty much came through, sheer blind luck. It's a similar premise to Ares Mix's idea of using an anime core to expand pose repertoire; as well as the dramatic dark lighting capacity from Experience.

Experience Realistic / Ares Mix / Deliberate

Liberty / URPM / Realistic Vision

Yesmix / Sparkling Nectar / Perfect World

I highly recommend this negative embedding. It has an extremely powerful effect on outputs, see the examples. From what I've seen it usually kills the ability to have dark images unless you use [x:n.n] to keep it off for a certain number of steps, which allows the model to set the scene. And it loves freckles, so be sure to neg that out if needed.

I initially didn't think this needed a VAE, most the example images don't have one active. The blonde lady and embedding on/off compares do. It's pretty acceptable without, but use the good ol' vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned to kick it up a notch.

I'll be adding the intermediate constituents of the mix to this post at some point, you can pop them through Supermerger to play with them or whatever. Mainly I just need to rescue some disk space.

If the anime model looks interesting, it'll be up soon. I was going to stick it here but maybe it's worth its own post.

items.name: PurePerfection
items.description:
PurePerfectionV2: I would like to express my gratitude to a helpful group of individuals who have assisted me in resolving numerous issues from the previous merge. In this update, I have incorporated an improved dataset consisting of photo-realistic images from MIdjourney V5.1 and General Google images.

I am confident that you will appreciate the enhancements made in this new version. The results I have achieved thus far have been truly remarkable. The level of detail in terms of skin, facial features, hands, pores, and the environment is nothing short of astonishing.

NOTE: Use a VAE, This is the one I use and the one most of the community uses

NOTE 2: Your results will vary based on settings used, please feel free to use my settings below


Sampling method | DPM++ SDE

Sampling Steps | 30

Hiresfix | Upscaler = Remacri, 0 Hires Steps, 2x upscale.

Denoising Strength | 0.4

CFG Scale | 6-8 Depends on what you prefer

Resolution base | 457x768

PurePerfectionV2 is a model that was created to address areas where other models lacked detail. It aims to introduce accurate skin tones, an aspect that most models lacked, and enables simple prompts to yield realistic results. I hope you all enjoy this model, If you like it, please leave a review. Furthermore, if this model receives enough attention, I will surpass expectations with V3 by training it using a larger quantity of higher-quality photos.

items.name: Mirabel Madrigal
items.description:
Please contact me here on civitAi or on Twitter if you want to provide the LoRa in a generation service.

TLDR (Because I don't care)

Use mirabel madrigal <lora:mirabelMadrigal_v1:1> in positiv promt.

If you like the LoRa, please feel free to share your generated images here and leave a review (or at least a rating) ;D

About

Well, I watched Encanto yesterday and Mirabel, the main character, was the only one I didn't get annoyed with, even though she's not the "all pretty" type girl... so I made a LoRa for her :D If you like musicals, you'll really like this film, I myself mostly skipped the music parts (without missing any data I could use for training, of course).

Training

I managed to get 75 shots to work with... I was a bit disappointed that she only wore 2 different outfits in the whole film (mostly her, normal clothes, and in one scene a nightgown, (okay, in theory 3 outfits, but I did not use her childhood scenes for training)).

Usage

No weight adjustments required:

mirabel madrigal <lora:mirabelMadrigal_v1:1>

You are able to put on and of her glasses and her normal outfit was tagged with white blose, long green skirt so if the model does not behave when putting her in a different outfit simply put these tags into the negative prompt.

items.description:
This Lora is designed to replicate a Gwyneth Paltrow from another universe and similarities to the one in the universe we occupy is coincidental and unintentional.

The trigger is "Gwen"

optimized for v1.5 but b/c 2.0 is trained on 1.5 it really doesn't matter what you use I put the same exact dumb prompt against a ton of checkpoints and got decent results, much better results then using Gwyneth Paltrow as the prompt.

I do not believe it is optimized for inpaint i guess let me know and also let me know if there are any other people from other universes similar to ours that I should make these for...also let me know if you hate it so I can do better.

I had a bunch of content for this dozens of pictures but apparently it might not be permitted. If it sucks please let me know so I can do better. Also to be clear this will not generate any NSFW pics unless the ckpt was trained on NSFW.

items.name: Dolly Little
items.description:
Dolly Little

is a retired American model, actress and cosplayer, born on May 25, 1995 in Texas. She lives up to her name by being a mere 4'9" (145cm) and weighing a scant 85lbs (39kg). She has intense red hair and an infectiously innocent smile. She was nominated for several industry awards in 2016. Dolly speaks French and credits Kota Skye as her role model, while her best friend is actress Elsa Jean. She performed in the industry for two years, from 2015 to 2017. Dolly expressed her desire to have a lesbian orgy on camera, but hasn't had the opportunity yet. Her favorite male performer to work with was Brick Danger, while her favorite female performer was Hope Harper. Dolly's fan base contributed to rescuing her from a very emotionally and financially abusive situation in Oregon, and she moved closer to her family and agency in Florida. She was nominated for several awards, including Customs Making Mogul of the Year and Cam Girl of the Year in 2016, Customs Specialist of the Year and Ravishing Redhead of the Year in 2017. Dolly grew up in Portland, Oregon, where she was studious in high school and played Friday Night Magic on weekends and hung out with D&D groups. She did a Cosplay of Jean Grey for SuperCon and has led Lightsaber Choreographies as both a Sith and a Jedi.

Generation Advice

Prompt and sampling

Most images have been generated with Lora settings at 1. All examples done with CyberRealistic v1.4. If you look at the description of most prompts, they are more about the theme and feel. This seems to generate great images every time for Dolly, close-ups, full body, etc.

Samples used 512x640 with hires fix @ 0.45-0.55 denoising either using Latent or 8x NMKD-Faces as upscaler. No restore faces used.

Works without, but use D011lyLittle as the trigger for more facial accuracy.

Upscaling

Ultimate SD upscale script used for all upscales ~.15 - .4 denoising.

Sidenote

Dolly Little is one of my personal favourites. This may be my best LORA yet, which is funny as I failed probably 4x generating this one over the past week or so. I also had to use D011yLittle as trigger word as typing DollyLittle would trigger doll like effects for some models. I have not tested this on any other model this time as I'm lazy, let me know how you go.

items.name: Centerfold Blend
items.description:
Like my work? Buy me a coffee!

This pet project is my custom mostly-NSFW, mostly-photorealistic model, blended and fine-tuned on hand-captioned images of people, both clothed and nude, primarily from professional photo shoots. My goal is to create a model that generates beautiful images of people by default without needing excessive prompts, so that your prompts can focus on adding qualities instead of removing defects.

I encourage you to try it without too many negative prompts, embeddings, or textual inversions first and only add those in as needed. You also may need to reduce the weight of LoRAs that impose similar effects as the model itself.

When you're going for photographic images, you may wish to place "illustration" in the negative prompts. The following negative prompts are usually good: "3D digital illustration, blurry, low quality, grainy, pixelated" But remember to take "illustration" out of the negative prompt if you're going for art/anime/comic style results.

Jackie is a custom character embedding for generating consistent character.

Jackie is a blond male model with androgynous features. He has an athletic male body and feminine face and hair. He works well for elf and vampire character generations.

This embedding is trained with dataset images that is generated by AI. He's not based on any existing person or character.

Training Info

Training Jackie was more difficult than training a woman character as AI loved converting Jackie into a woman. So I used an aggressive training with 5 images instead of my usual 25 and used a lower training step to end training before AI could turn him into female.

Yes, it's a full checkpoint as tagged. If you like lora stuff and feel that's on par w/ DB for likenesses or have limited resources, this download probably isn't for you.

For best results use Hires Fix. For ultimate results use in tandem w/ 30-60% the steps modified by Controlnet w/ Canny, Openpose, or shuffle. Controlnet.

SAMPLES WERE GENERATED W/ CONTROLNET (if you don't understand what that means you will probably be disappointed).


I find it fun to put actual movie still frames in the CN input and use it for the first half or the generation. If you have a quick system try turning on Generate forever w/ 2 or 3 selected for the batch. While it's running you can change the prompts and CN input/settings and A1111 will update and continue churning out generations.

34 images, 20 steps, 13 epochs, you find many epochs (with test images using plot xy script) on my Patreon while supporting me.

For some of the images i used ControlNet Poses Pack that you can download from my creator page, just search for poses in my model page if you want to replicate these images.

Enjoy!

items.name: Oversized Jacket
items.description:
Get early access to build and test build, be able to try all epochs and test them by yourself on Patreon or contact me for support on Discord

Training settings:

35 images, 20 steps, 12 epochs, you find many epochs (with test images using plot xy script) on my Patreon while supporting me.

items.name: JMG Style LoCon
items.description:
V1:

A LoRA for JMG's Style based on Any-L.

Shouldn't need any trigger words, however adding 'jmg' or 'jmg style', may force the style more. Works best at weight 0.8-1.0. Clip Skip 2, however it is not required to generate good images. Trained on booru tags. Good SFW & NSFW. Currently over represents large proportions, so use some negatives.

For best results, or results similar to mine, please use Any models or a similar anime-style model. Additionally, it is most recommended to use badv3/EasyNegative textual inversions.

Should work fine with other LoRAs.

Examples done using CounterfeitV3.0. Follow prompts to attempt replication and use given negatives for better generations.

Usage:

  • CFG Scale: 7-9

  • LoRA Weight: 0.6-0.8, 1.0

  • Should work fine for less detailed prompts. High-res fix is highly recommended

items.name: BimbostyleFiveU (DeliberateV2) LORA
items.description:
This time i tried to generate a Lora that produces extreme overfilled saline/expander breasts, wider hips and thicker lips. Can be used to transform persons into a more bimbo look

The model trained for comic Style is coming Later today or tomorrow(i need to generate the previews first)

This is model uses the exact same input as bimbostyleFive but was trained on deliberate_V2 which hopefully means that it's better applicable to other .ckpt in comparison to the normal "Five"

Since i mainly use "art style" ckpt i can't really say anything about the full potential of this Lora on other ckpt.

Combining this Lora together with One/Two/Three/Four in a "art style" ckpt i.e. revAnimated give interesting results and i can only recommend trying it out. (i don't know if the same applies to "real" ones as well)

If you mix my models, i would recommend to always put the stronger weighted Lora in the front. i.e.

<lora:bimbostyleFiveU:0.75>:<lora:bimbostyleTwo:0.25>

And, at least for me, going over a total strength of 1 would result in heavy artefacts

This is a New Style Lora I have created, it is suitable for cartoon especially manga styles.

Interesting thing about this model is it's sort of balance between realistic and cartoon, therefore I suggest you to go and play with it see which one you like. The training data is mostly from the manga images I have found online :)

I will suggest using 0.7 to 0.9 weight for this Lora. Using weight above 1 can look over fitting.

In the example images I used the same prompt and experiment with different Models.
